@startuml C4_Concern_Reliability
!include https://raw.githubusercontent.com/plantuml-stdlib/C4-PlantUML/master/C4_Component.puml

title YAWL Cross-Cutting Concern - Reliability & Redundancy

Boundary(availability, "Availability Strategy") {
    Component(active_active, "Active-Active", "HA", "All nodes active")
    Component(active_passive, "Active-Passive", "DR", "Standby ready")
    Component(load_balancing, "LoadBalancing", "Distribution", "Traffic routing")
}

Boundary(redundancy, "Redundancy Levels") {
    Component(single_node, "Single Node", "Dev", "Single point of failure")
    Component(n_plus_one, "N+1 Redundancy", "Prod", "One failure tolerance")
    Component(n_plus_two, "N+2 Redundancy", "Critical", "Two failure tolerance")
}

Boundary(failure_modes, "Failure Mode Analysis") {
    Component(hardware_failure, "Hardware Failure", "Type", "Server crash")
    Component(network_failure, "Network Failure", "Type", "Connection loss")
    Component(software_bug, "Software Bug", "Type", "Logic error")
    Component(data_corruption, "DataCorruption", "Type", "Bad state")
}

Boundary(recovery, "Recovery Mechanisms") {
    Component(checkpointing, "Checkpointing", "State", "Save snapshots")
    Component(replication, "Replication", "Data", "Multiple copies")
    Component(failover, "Failover", "Automatic", "Switch to backup")
    Component(rollback, "Rollback", "Recovery", "Restore from checkpoint")
}

Boundary(slas, "SLA Targets") {
    Component(availability_99_9, "99.9% Availability", "Target", "8.76 hours/year downtime")
    Component(rto, "RTO <1 hour", "Target", "Recovery time")
    Component(rpo, "RPO <5 minutes", "Target", "Data loss window")
    Component(mtbf, "MTBF >1000 hours", "Target", "Mean time between failures")
}

active_active --> load_balancing: Uses
active_passive --> failover: Uses
n_plus_one --> redundancy: Requires
n_plus_two --> redundancy: Requires
hardware_failure --> failover: Detected by
network_failure --> failover: Detected by
software_bug --> rollback: Uses
data_corruption --> checkpointing: Prevents
replication --> rpo: Determines

Note as N1
Reliability Strategy:

Availability:
- Active-Active: All nodes serve traffic
- Active-Passive: One active, one standby
- Load Balancer: Distributes requests

Redundancy Levels:

Development:
- Single node (acceptable)
- RTO: N/A
- RTO: N/A

Production:
- N+1 redundancy (one failure tolerance)
- 2 nodes minimum
- RTO: <1 hour
- RPO: <5 minutes

Critical Systems:
- N+2 redundancy (two failures)
- 3+ nodes minimum
- RTO: <15 minutes
- RPO: <1 minute

Failure Detection:
- Heartbeat every 30 seconds
- Failure confirmed after 2 missed beats
- Automatic failover within 60 seconds

Recovery Mechanisms:
- Checkpointing: Save state every 5 min
- Replication: Real-time sync to standby
- Failover: Auto-switch on failure
- Rollback: Restore from checkpoint

SLA Targets:
- Availability: 99.9% (8.76 hrs/yr downtime)
- RTO: <1 hour
- RPO: <5 minutes
- MTBF: >1000 hours (not failing every 6 weeks)

Monitoring:
- Heartbeat monitoring
- Recovery metrics
- Failover testing (quarterly)
- Incident review (weekly)

Testing:
- Chaos engineering (inject failures)
- Failover drills (monthly)
- Data recovery tests (quarterly)
- Whole-system simulations (yearly)
End note

SHOW_LEGEND()
@enduml
